ratings.comment: Gives an attitude that seems like she doesn't like being asked questions in class, but she'll help you outside of class or before /end of lecture. Is sometimes unprepared and not sure exactly how an equation is suppose to be written, like with a negative sign or not, and tells you to just read the book. Overall okay.

I understand that it's an engineering course and should be hard. However,  the length of the exams is ridiculous. You are not able to finish them all in class time(50 mins). Could have done better if extra time was given for sure.

She's a young professor so still improving, but  offers a lot of resources and seems very willing to help you understand things better. Not perfect, makes mistakes in class, and gives ridiculous tests (only able to finish half the problems in the time allotted) but gives a nice curve. Also really kind and seems to actually care.
